Distant Worlds Universe REFRESHED EM Version (DWUR-EM)

/========== About ==========\
Now that Distant Worlds Universe Refreshed is several years old, I am looking to revisit some of the assets and features. This new version of DWUR leans into the expanded capabilities of DWU from Alvek's Expansion Mod. Enjoy!
-- Salemonz

v0.9.2 -- 14 Mar 2026 -- Updated pirate portraits (included legendary option for EM)
v0.9.1 -- 12 Mar 2026 -- Updated engine exhaust graphics
v0.9.0 -- 04 Mar 2026 -- Initial beta release

/========== What's New ==========\
- Fixed the "overshadow" problem with planets and shadow textures being too large
- Added the new facility "Diplomatic Center" to the game (per ExpansionMod). Diplomatic Center increases the chance for ambassadors to spawn in empire.
- Re-worked many race portraits (25 races)...some to bring them in line with Distant Worlds 2 art direction...some because I wanted to.
- Re-worked hyperdeny graphic for better visability
- Re-worked some UI elements (character icons, mainly) for better visibility

/========== Installation ==========\
1. Download and install Alvek's Expansion Mod (EM) via his Github here: https://github.com/DW-UX/DistantWorldsExpanded. Please pay attention to the instructions (especially the need to unblock the .zip before opening) to correctly install EM.
2. Download DWUR from https://gitlab.com/dw2-refreshed-mods/dwur-em-version.
3. Create a directory for the mod within your Distant Worlds: Universe folder's CUSTOMIZATION directory...you can call this whatever you'd like.
4. Unpack the downloaded DWUR archive into the directory you created in step 3.
5. Launch the game.
6. Go to "Change Theme"
7. Pick the name of the directory you created in step 3 and click Activate Theme.
(The game might hang for up to a minute while everything loads)
8. Exit the game and restart (even though the game loads the files after clicking "Activate Theme", it only partially loads...I don't know why DW:U is like this...I'm not a developer :D You need to exit the game and restart after activating the theme.)
9. You'll know the mod is fully activated by seeing the custom DWUR background and hearing the music (if you have your music volume turned on)
10. Enjoy!